cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL 

This paper is about the behavior of a convolutional neural net in a setting that introduces classification tasks sequentially. The paper discusses the net's ability to master new tasks while preserving mastery of previously learned tasks, which is a key aspect of metalearning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image classification tasks, which falls under the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
